commit_message:
[Verify] Configure 'catalog_type' in 'data-processing' section

Sahara has two service types: 'data_processing' and 'data-processing'.
'data_processing' is deprecated, but it can be used in previous OpenStack
releases. So we need to configure the 'catalog_type' option to support
environments where 'data_processing' is used as service type for Sahara.

Change-Id: Iddd8da9dcde7ab0e0ea4f315fe78965e9b2474ec

subject: Place bootloader onto /boot partition-less disks
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-28 17:16:03.000000000', 'files': ['fuel_agent/drivers/nailgun.py', 'fuel_agent/tests/test_nailgun.py'], 'message': "Place bootloader onto /boot partition-less disks

Sometimes, there's no separate /boot fs image. Therefore,
a bootloader should have been installed onto disk where
rootfs image lands.

It seems that Nailgun driver didn't support such cases and then
an expection regarding missing /boot partition was thrown.

That was totally wrong approach. Nailgun driver should work fine
without /boot partition if there's no /boot image.

In addition, this change removes ugly hacks from Ironic driver.
Apparently Ironic driver explicitly sets self._boot_done and
self._boot_partition_done flags to True, hence enables to bypass
that exception. Since now, Nailgun can handle such a case, so
there're no any needs to keep that hack in Ironic driver.

Change-Id: I2d97fec7810643865abf0414f2cb80da1c591398
Closes-Bug: #1529066
"}]
commit_message:
Place bootloader onto /boot partition-less disks

Sometimes, there's no separate /boot fs image. Therefore,
a bootloader should have been installed onto disk where
rootfs image lands.

It seems that Nailgun driver didn't support such cases and then
an expection regarding missing /boot partition was thrown.

That was totally wrong approach. Nailgun driver should work fine
without /boot partition if there's no /boot image.

In addition, this change removes ugly hacks from Ironic driver.
Apparently Ironic driver explicitly sets self._boot_done and
self._boot_partition_done flags to True, hence enables to bypass
that exception. Since now, Nailgun can handle such a case, so
there're no any needs to keep that hack in Ironic driver.

Change-Id: I2d97fec7810643865abf0414f2cb80da1c591398
Closes-Bug: #1529066

old version of rpc api ( < 1.19) so heatclient call
new api methods that doesn't exist. In this case get stack

subject: Convergence: Config option for thread pool size
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-24 09:18:45.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/worker.py', 'heat/common/config.py', 'heat/engine/service.py'], 'message': 'Convergence: Config option for thread pool size

Add an option for setting executor_thread_pool_size for convergence
worker service. By default, the value is set to 64 by oslo.messaging and
it causes lot of "QueuePool limit exceeded" error.

Since, by default, the maximum DB sessions that could be opened
simultaneously will be 15 (5 is max_pool_size and 10 is max_overflow),
the worker thread pool size should be set accordingly. After some
investigation (report in bug comments), I found the value is better set
to 8 or 10 as default. Of course, this value should be properly set by
user depending on resources available.

Change-Id: I2c2aa3f14bb31908b46cf82e729410fa42e14931
Closes-Bug: #1491185
'}]
commit_message:
Convergence: Config option for thread pool size

Add an option for setting executor_thread_pool_size for convergence
worker service. By default, the value is set to 64 by oslo.messaging and
it causes lot of "QueuePool limit exceeded" error.

Since, by default, the maximum DB sessions that could be opened
simultaneously will be 15 (5 is max_pool_size and 10 is max_overflow),
the worker thread pool size should be set accordingly. After some
investigation (report in bug comments), I found the value is better set
to 8 or 10 as default. Of course, this value should be properly set by
user depending on resources available.

Change-Id: I2c2aa3f14bb31908b46cf82e729410fa42e14931
Closes-Bug: #1491185

commit_message:
Do not use notify for db-sync from main init class

If we want to use db-sync only on some node (for example, primary node)
and don't want run it on another we will get resource not found error
for notify in package ironic-common on db-sync.

Also db/sync class already contains all needed notifies on ironic-package
tag, so it also is duplicate.

Change-Id: I29939384bf96b82d9124307222a239b8aa95336b
Related-bug: #1529046

commit_message:
Fix handling of default node network group in Fuel UI

To check if node network group is default group,
'is_default' attribute of node network group should be used
instead of comparing with 'default' node networ group name

Related-Bug: #1508973

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-26 11:24:04.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/hitachi/hnas_backend.py', 'cinder/image/image_utils.py', 'cinder/volume/drivers/emc/emc_vmax_masking.py', 'cinder/utils.py', 'cinder/scheduler/host_manager.py', 'cinder/volume/api.py'], 'message': 'Wrong usage of "a"

Wrong usage of "a" in the mesages:
"Convert list of dicts to a indexted dict"
"Attempt to create a initiatorGroup"
"Return a empty"
"Return a object containing the parsed output"
"where volume is either a dict or a oslo_versionedobject"
"this is a update from legacy driver"

Should be:
"Convert list of dicts to an indexted dict"
"Attempt to create an initiatorGroup"
"Return an empty"
"Return an object containing the parsed output"
"where volume is either a dict or an oslo_versionedobject"
"this is an update from legacy driver"

Totally 6 occasions in Cinder base code.

Change-Id: I209fa7817f531107ae15a980f81c02fe63dd557e
'}]
commit_message:
Wrong usage of "a"

Wrong usage of "a" in the mesages:
"Convert list of dicts to a indexted dict"
"Attempt to create a initiatorGroup"
"Return a empty"
"Return a object containing the parsed output"
"where volume is either a dict or a oslo_versionedobject"
"this is a update from legacy driver"

Should be:
"Convert list of dicts to an indexted dict"
"Attempt to create an initiatorGroup"
"Return an empty"
"Return an object containing the parsed output"
"where volume is either a dict or an oslo_versionedobject"
"this is an update from legacy driver"

Totally 6 occasions in Cinder base code.

Change-Id: I209fa7817f531107ae15a980f81c02fe63dd557e

commit_message:
Fix handling of default node network group in Fuel UI

To check if node network group is default group,
'is_default' attribute of node network group should be used
instead of comparing with 'default' node networ group name

W/o this fix, the command "proc_kill pid name count" will misplace

commit_message:
Fix the proc_kill ocf helper func

W/o this fix, the command "proc_kill pid name count" will misplace
the passed count of tries as the signal name for the pkill, which
is wrong and might be unpredictably harmful for the proces group
containing the given pid.

The fix is to correctly specify params for the proc_kill calls.
Add bats tests for the proc_kill as well.

Closes-bug: #1528889

Change-Id: I992480f4e0d3380215d3f8bd910553070334c343
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Add GLARE to Fuel Web UI

This patch adds support for glance artifact repository feature to Fuel
WEB. This feature is added as experimental and placed in 'additional
services' section as far as the only one component which use it this
time is murano.

commit_message:
Adjust rspec tests for retries in openstacklib.

A patch in openstacklib[1] broke the some rspec test in keystone.  This
adjust the test to match the new behavior of the lib.

The request_timeout is fixed to 0 so that only one retry is done.
Failure to do that would make the number of retries unknown and the time
spend on the three failing tests around 60 seconds each.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/puppet-openstacklib/commit/701b6fe0acf56e9132e9b0a448f28670c714cedb

Change-Id: I6adc439a806cf209e2fae35446a15b07353a18c2
Closes-Bug: #1529371
